'''Ozu Shrine''' (おづじんじゃ) is a shrine {{jalink|enshrined}} in Koyama, {{jalink|Tado-chō|Q7674654}}, {{jalink|Kuwana|Q496472}}, {{jalink|Mie Prefecture|Q128196}}. It is an {{jalink|Engishiki shrine}}, and its former rank was {{jalink|Sonsha|Q134917284}}.

=== Origin and history ===
Ozu Shrine is one of the fifteen shrines of {{jalink|Kuwana District|Q1131489}} in {{jalink|Ise Province|Q864166}}. In the first year of {{jalink|Ninju|Q1373077}} under {{jalink|Emperor Montoku|Q357225}}, it was granted Junior Sixth Rank Lower<ref>{{Cite book|和書|title=多度町史|publisher=多度教育委員会|page=54}}</ref>, and was eventually promoted to Junior Fifth Rank Upper<ref>{{Cite web|title=三重県神社庁 尾津神社（小山）|url=http://kyoka.mie-jinjacho.or.jp/shrine/%e5%b0%be%e6%b4%a5%e7%a5%9e%e7%a4%be%ef%bc%88%e5%b0%8f%e5%b1%b1%ef%bc%89/|access-date=2025-11-30}}</ref>. In March {{jalink|1918|Q2088}} (Taishō 7), Yama Shrine, Sagun Shrine, and Hachiryū Daimyōjin were merged into it<ref>{{Cite web|title=県神社庁|url=https://jinja-net.jp/jinjacho-mie/jsearch3mie.php?jinjya=63095|access-date=2025-11-30}}</ref>.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* Principal deities: {{jalink|Yamato Takeru|Q333348|Yamato Takeru no Mikoto}}, Ashikagamiwake-no-Mikoto
* Associated deities: {{jalink|Ōyamatsumi|Q386563|Ōyamatsumi-no-Kami}}, one unidentified deity

=== Annual festival ===
October 11

=== Other ===
Clergy duties are concurrently administered by {{jalink|Tado Taisha|Q116140}}<ref>{{Cite web|title=尾津神社|url=https://jinja-net.jp/ozu-jinja2/|access-date=2025-11-30}}</ref>

